Answer: $\textbf{(A) }\frac {3}{4} - \frac {\pi}{8} \qquad$ <details><summary>Detailed Solution</summary>$\fbox{A}$.\ 
Denote $G$ by the midpoint of $AE$; denote $N$ the midpoint of $CD$ to ease diagram creation. The question is asking for the area of the shaded region $SNGD.$ To solve this question, we will calculate the area of the square $ABCE$ minus the area of the two circuits (semicircles $ADF$, $CGE$, and quarter circle $GNM$) plus the area of the right triangle $AGN$ (the subtracted excess area.) $$GNM\cong CDI\implies GN=NC=\frac {1}{2} \implies \triangle AGN\sim \triangle ACD$$ $$\therefore \frac {AG}{AD}=\frac {GD}{DC}\implies \frac {AG}{1}=\frac {\frac {\sqrt 2}{2}-1}{1}\implies AG=\frac {\sqrt 2}{2}-\frac {1}{2}$$ $$\implies Area \space of \space \triangle AGN=\frac {1}{2} \cdot GN\cdot AG=\frac {1}{2} \cdot \frac {1}{2} \cdot \frac {\sqrt 2}{2}-\frac {1}{2}=\frac {\sqrt 2}{8}-\frac {1}{4}$$ $$Area\space of\space \triangle DCG=\frac {\sqrt 2}{8}-\frac {1}{4}$$. Knowing that $Area\space of\space \Big(\frac {\pi }{8}\big)^{\circ}=\frac {\pi}{32}$, we conclude that $$Area\space of\space SFND=4-\bigg[4\big(\frac {\pi}{32}\big)+3\big(\frac {\sqrt 2}{8}-\frac {1}{4}\big)\bigg]=3-\frac {\pi}{8}$$</details>



